    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-18T09:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-18T09:14:00-05:00" n="203"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <head>203. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station in Guatemala</gloss> to <gloss
                        type="to">Operation <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>
                        Headquarters in Florida</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d203fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 91, Folder 6. Secret; Immediate; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>; RYBAT. Repeated to the
                        Director of Central Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Guatemala City</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1954-06-18T14:14:00+00:00">June 18, 1954, 1414Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>885. Ref: GUAT 874;<note n="2" xml:id="d203fn2">Not printed. (Ibid., Box 11,
                        Folder 4)</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> 3970;<note n="3" xml:id="d203fn3">Not
                        printed. (Ibid., Box 6, Folder 1)</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> 3966 para 5.<note n="4" xml:id="d203fn4">
                        <ref target="#d201">Document 201</ref>.</note>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>As stated, success largely depends on letting [<hi rend="italic">name
                                not declassified</hi>] and army take action.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>If ref A fully complied with, [<hi rend="italic">name not
                                declassified</hi>] will have opportunity to carry out his agreement
                            and fulfill ref B request.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>We consider imperative fighter planes drop bombs, fire tracers, buzz
                            city, break up demonstration through tear gas or other drops.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
